FBIS3-48113 "dreas015_c_94043" FBIS-EAS-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 North Korea Achievements in Railway Transport Reported SK1801102694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1007 GMT 18 Jan 94 SK1801102694 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The railway transport workers of Korea are registering significant achievements in their efforts to carry out the tasks set forth by the great leader President Kim Il-song in his New Year address. According to data available at the Ministry of Railways, 120,000 more tons of freight than in the last fifteen days of 1993 were transported in the first half of January. In this period the General Bureau of Kaechon Railways carried 45,000 more tons of freight by organising and commanding transportation meticulously and cutting the stoppage time of waggons. The General Bureau of Eastern Railways has fulfilled its daily quotas at 113.1 percent. The General Bureau of Western and Northern Railways carried 2,000 to 3,000 more tons of freight than their daily assignments through effective control of equipment and technical control and energetic "drive for extra-haulage on schedule without accident to implement the decision of the 18th plenary meeting of the Fifth Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea." The Kim Chong-tae general electric locomotive works, the June 4 general rolling stock works and other plants are supplying in good time equipment and materials needed for railway transport.
